{Black's last move was 8...b7-b6. How should we continue, based on my
recommendation in the theoretical chapter?} 9. h4 $1 {[%csl Rg7,Rg8][%cal
Gh4h5,Rh5h6]} h5 (9... Bb7 10. e5 $1 {White shuts down the g7-bishop and is
about to continue with h4-h5, where Black's position would be rather tough to
defend.}) 10. Bg5 {[%csl Gg5] And the g5-square becomes a lovely outpost for
our pieces as ...f7-f6 would clearly weaken Black's position too much.} *

