{Black's last move was ...Bg4, putting a lot of pressure on our center. What
is the typical way to meet this continuation?} 12. d5 $1 {The rook on a1 is
not a problem at all!} Ne5 (12... Bxa1 13. Qxa1 Na5 14. Bh6 {White regains the
sacrificed material with a nice yield, forcing Black to make a weakening move.
..f7-f6. See the theoretical chapter on 7...O-O for more details!}) 13. Nxe5
Bxe2 14. Qxe2 Bxe5 15. Rab1 $36 {White's extra pawn in the center and his
initiative on the queenside provide him with a clear advantage.} *

