{[%evp 0,9,81,19,6,3,88,26,103,100,112,115]} {[#]} 11. a4 $1 {White stops the
plan of ...a7-a6 followed by ...b7-b5 and gets a large advantage.} a6 (11...
Qxc3 $2 12. Bd2 Qb2 13. Re2 $1 {Creates a threat of trapping the queen by
means of Be1/Ba5 and pretty much wins the game.}) 12. Bf1 Rd8 13. Qb3 e6 14.
Bg5 Re8 {Up to this point White played well, and what he did in the game was
fine, but it would have been even stronger to shut down the Black g7-bishop by
means of} 15. e5 $1 {Black's position is truly disastrous. One obvious idea to
mention is Nd2-c4-d6, the opponent has a very hard time stopping it. Another
plan would be h2-h4-h5, followed by an attack against the Black barely
protected king.} *

