{[#] Black to play! What is his key defensive idea?} 15... Qb4 $1 {The key
nuance which was pointed out by Svidler. The point of this move is that Black
wants us to castle, which worsens our king's position as the endgame is
approaching and we would like to keep it in the center.} (15... Qxd2+ $2 16.
Kxd2 $1 O-O-O+ 17. Ke3 $14 {The White king is doing a much better job in the
center rather than on g1, that is why Black's 15th move is so important.}) 16.
O-O Qxd2 17. Nxd2 O-O-O 18. Nb3 Bxb3 19. axb3 Kc7 20. Rxc5 Rd6 $11 {And Black
finally equalizes.} *

